It had it good points. But it hand a ton of flaws, including the butchering of Alucard's character.

The best Castlevania is more likely to be Super Castlevania IV or Lords Of Shadow.

@SynthWaveFox0 I can explain why I think that Castlevania SOTN cannot be the best Castlevania and has flaws that I find it incomprehensible that the fans did not complain more than that. First, the general design of the game, I do not appreciate this manga style, I think it doesn't stick to the atmosphere of castlevania. Second, why do alucard has NO frame of invincibility it's really annoying and SOTN is not the only one all other IGAvania have this very annoying problem. Then, the enemies That pushes you outside the screen is annoying, very annoying. but the worst is the selection of items in the inventory That is really the WORST in all the games I ever played.

Finally, when I played SOTN I had the impression to deal with a sub-super metroid instead of a true castlevania. I think there was a way to make a metroidvania more faithful to the first games. It's not for nothing that I had not played any castlevania between circle of the moon and lords of shadow. I'm not saying SOTN is a bad game, but it has flaws and that it is not a masterpiece, it is just a very good game, that's all.

Oh, and I apologize if I have mistakes because my first language is not English and I have to translate everything, so understand.
